        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-10 13:42:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nAlexis, although I would like to see the DB files gone from our config, this commit will disable persistent storage for policy db.\nThere was a requirement (for resiliency) to make DB storage persistent. Otherwise upon pod restart the DB data will be gone.\nI opened a bug to policy team (https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-207) but they claimed it to be feature request and closed it.\nBottom line, if you remove the PV, we have no persistence to Policy DB, which is not in line with Beijing aspirations of resilient ONAP.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
