        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-14 07:57:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nI think it is because of the large difference between the drools logback.xml files.\nMichael, please advise, how should the drools logback.xml file be changed in order to provide canonicalized, useful data at /var/log/onap.\nBTW, I see no special problem with /var/log/onap. it is mounted in both drools and filebeat as emptyDir, which shouldn't cause any problem. I would expect same exceptions in 'log' directory.",
        "patchset_number": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "4fb68a50667b079eb085e2c848fdad9761a701a1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 497,
          "name": "Borislav Glozman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "borislav.glozman@amdocs.com",
          "username": "BorislavG"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-14 10:51:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\n> > (1 comment)\n > \n > I think it is because of the large difference between the drools\n > logback.xml files.\n > Michael, please advise, how should the drools logback.xml file be\n > changed in order to provide canonicalized, useful data at\n > /var/log/onap.\n > BTW, I see no special problem with /var/log/onap. it is mounted in\n > both drools and filebeat as emptyDir, which shouldn't cause any\n > problem. I would expect same exceptions in 'log' directory.\n\nI applied your patch on my env and it works OK with /var/log/onap:\n[root@kubernetes-master ~]# kubectl get pods -n kroko-policy\nNAME                       READY     STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\nbrmsgw-1600721431-4psp5    1/1       Running   0          1h\ndrools-3111157934-c2s86    2/2       Running   0          1h\nmariadb-3164033838-7lms8   1/1       Running   0          1h\nnexus-2483527695-z3w4q     1/1       Running   0          1h\npap-3535127949-s81cr       2/2       Running   0          1h\npdp-989875794-57gw2        2/2       Running   0          1h\n[root@kubernetes-master ~]# kubectl exec -ti -n kroko-policy drools-3111157934-c2s86 -- ls /var/log/onap\nDefaulting container name to drools.\nUse 'kubectl describe pod/drools-3111157934-c2s86' to see all of the containers in this pod.\ndebug.log  error.log  network.log\n\nNo error in pod log.",
        "patchset_number": 10
      },
